5. Product boundaries

Do not let Theia replace:
- KaixuSuper-IDE landing and IDE pages
- existing editor and explorer model
- GitHub and SCM integration logic
- admin and policy surfaces

Use Theia only to augment:
- launcher and app switching
- file and workspace support
- terminal and background tasks
- autonomous coding workflows

6. Acceptance criteria

KaixuSuperIDEia is done when:
- the original KaixuSuper-IDE still exists as-is.
- the upgraded build launches as a full app, never a preview widget.
- Theia adds coding support power without overwriting the product shell.
- users can launch code tasks, workspaces, and app modules smoothly from the upgraded build.

7. Delivery sequence

Phase 1
- scaffold wrapper and bridge files

Phase 2
- add launcher/runtime process control

Phase 3
- connect module bridges to support-layer services

Phase 4
- register KaixuSuperIDEia beside the original platform in the 0s catalog

Phase 5
- test launch, coding workflows, and operational stability